# Momentum Design System

## Vibe / Philosophy

Momentum feels like **mission control software**, not a wellness app. The UI should feel like a high-stakes operational dashboard — precise, data-forward, clinical. No decorative illustrations, no celebration animations, no cheerful gradients. Execution is acknowledged with green. Everything else is zinc and shadow.

- All-caps labels with letter spacing for section headers, tab names, tier headings
- Data comes first — numbers and states are larger than their labels
- Dark surfaces with subtle depth (not flat, not glassmorphic unless explicitly noted)
- Micro-interactions through haptics (`expo-haptics`), not bouncy animations
- Screens are named STATUS, LOG, SIGNAL, SYSTEM — never Home, Calendar, Journal, Chat

---

## Color Palette

All colors live in `lib/theme.ts`. Never use raw hex strings in components — import from theme.

```typescript
// lib/theme.ts — canonical colors
export const colors = {
  // Surfaces
  base:           '#09090B',  // Root background (near-black)
  card:           '#111113',  // Card / elevated surface
  input:          '#18181B',  // Input fields, code blocks
  overlay:        '#000000CC', // Modal backdrop (80% opacity)

  // Primary accent — emerald execution color
  accent:         '#10B981',  // Emerald — execution success, primary CTAs
  accentMuted:    'rgba(16,185,129,0.15)', // Selected/active states
  accentDim:      'rgba(16,185,129,0.08)', // Subtle tint backgrounds

  // Momentum Index gauge — blue (metric/data indicator, distinct from action accent)
  indexBlue:      '#3B82F6',  // Momentum Index circular gauge ring
  indexBlueMuted: 'rgba(59,130,246,0.15)',

  // Text
  textPrimary:    '#FAFAFA',  // Body, headings
  textSecondary:  '#A1A1AA',  // Supporting info, subtitles
  textMuted:      '#52525B',  // Labels, placeholders, disabled

  // Borders
  border:         '#27272A',  // Default border
  borderActive:   'rgba(16,185,129,0.3)', // Focused/active input border

  // Execution status
  statusDone:     '#10B981',  // Emerald — fully executed
  statusPartial:  '#A1A1AA',  // Neutral gray — partial
  statusSkipped:  '#27272A',  // Very dark — skipped
  statusMissed:   '#3F3F46',  // Dark zinc — missed (blends back)

