## Component Patterns

### Cards

```tsx
// Standard card — non-interactive
<View style={{ backgroundColor: colors.card, borderRadius: radius.md, padding: spacing.md, borderWidth: 1, borderColor: colors.border }}>
  {children}
</View>

// Pressable card
<Pressable style={({ pressed }) => ({ backgroundColor: colors.card, borderRadius: radius.md, padding: spacing.md, borderWidth: 1, borderColor: colors.border, opacity: pressed ? 0.75 : 1 })}>
  {children}
</Pressable>
```

### Protocol Row

```tsx
// Protocol item inside Protocols section
// - Left: circular checkbox (empty = border only, done = accent fill + checkmark)
// - Center: title + metadata (time, tier)
// - Right: kebab menu (3 dots)
// Completed state: title in textSecondary, checkbox in accent color
```

### Section Header

```tsx
// All section labels follow this pattern
<View style={{ flexDirection: 'row', justifyContent: 'space-between', alignItems: 'center', marginBottom: spacing.sm }}>
  <Text style={[typography.micro, { color: colors.textSecondary }]}>SECTION TITLE</Text>
  <Pressable><Text style={[typography.caption, { color: colors.accent }]}>Action</Text></Pressable>
</View>
```

### Tier Divider

```tsx
// Tier label inside protocol list (NON-NEGOTIABLE, GROWTH, ROTATING FOCUS)
<View style={{ flexDirection: 'row', alignItems: 'center', gap: spacing.xs, marginVertical: spacing.sm }}>
  <View style={{ width: 6, height: 6, borderRadius: 3, backgroundColor: colors.tierNonNeg }} />
  <Text style={[typography.micro, { color: colors.textMuted }]}>NON-NEGOTIABLE</Text>
</View>
```

### Primary Button

```tsx
<Pressable style={{ backgroundColor: colors.accent, borderRadius: radius.md, paddingVertical: spacing.sm + 4, alignItems: 'center' }}>
  <Text style={{ color: '#000', fontWeight: fontWeights.semibold, fontSize: 15 }}>Label</Text>
</Pressable>
```

### Momentum Index Card

```tsx
// Top card on STATUS tab
// - Large score number in systemScore style
// - Delta (+1.2%) in accent color if positive, red if negative
// - Circular gauge ring in indexBlue
// - "LAST COMPUTED" and "DELTA" metadata in micro style, textMuted
// - Score label (LOCKED IN / BUILDING / DRIFTING / OFF TRACK) in caption style
```

Score label thresholds:
- 80–100 → `LOCKED IN` (accent color)
- 60–79 → `BUILDING` (indexBlue)
- 40–59 → `DRIFTING` (amber `#F59E0B`)
- 0–39 → `OFF TRACK` (red `#EF4444`)

### Mission Briefing Card

```tsx
// Dark card, slightly different from standard card
// Header row: "AI GENERATED • TODAY" in micro style (cyan #06B6D4)
// Title: bold, textPrimary, ~17px
// Body: body style, textSecondary
// Priority List: bullet-style list items in caption style
// Two action buttons at bottom: "Contextual Chat" (ghost) + "Start Day" (filled blue)
```

### Bottom Navigation

5 tabs: Mission | Plan | + (FAB center) | Chat | Menu

- Active tab: accent color icon + label
- Inactive: textMuted icon + label
- Center FAB: large `+` button in accent color with circular background
- Tab labels: `micro` typography

### Coaching Style Cards (Onboarding)

```tsx
// Each coaching style (DIRECT / STRATEGIC / DRIVEN) is a pressable card
// Selected: border in that style's accent color, subtle accent background tint
// Icon in style accent color, label in bold, description in textSecondary
// "TONE PREVIEW" section inside: small blockquote example in textMuted
```

### Calibration Sliders

```tsx
// Each metric has a colored gradient track
// Thumb is white circle with shadow
// Value displayed prominently on the right (large number, bold)
// Label above with icon (colored per metric) + description below in caption/textMuted
// Scale labels at ends (e.g., "1 — POOR" → "5 — AVG" → "10 — EXCELLENT")
```

### Execution Calendar (LOG Tab)

```tsx
// Month grid
// Each cell background color:
//   All complete → dark emerald tint
//   Partial      → amber/dark gold tint
//   Missed       → dark crimson tint
//   No data      → colors.card
//   Today        → indexBlue (bright blue highlight)
// Small dots below date number indicate protocol count
// Legend block at bottom explains color coding
```

