## NativeWind Usage

This project uses **NativeWind v4** with Tailwind CSS.

- Prefer NativeWind class strings for layout and spacing
- Use `lib/theme.ts` color tokens via `style={{ color: colors.accent }}` for semantic colors (do not hardcode Tailwind color classes for brand colors)
- Custom colors should be extended in `tailwind.config.js` to match theme tokens
- Use `className` for spacing/layout; use `style` for dynamic/programmatic values

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD
<View className="flex-1 px-4 gap-2" style={{ backgroundColor: colors.card }}>

// ❌ BAD — hardcoded hex
<View style={{ backgroundColor: '#111113', paddingHorizontal: 16 }}>
```

---

## Animation & Interaction

- Use `react-native-reanimated` for any animated values — not `Animated` from React Native core
- Haptic feedback on all primary interactions: `Haptics.impactAsync(Haptics.ImpactFeedbackStyle.Light)`
- Protocol check-off: `Medium` haptics
- Avoid bounce/spring animations — prefer `timing` with `Easing.out(Easing.ease)`
- No confetti, celebration particles, or reward animations

---

## What to Avoid

- ❌ Rounded pill buttons for primary CTAs (use `radius.md` = 10, not full pill)
- ❌ Light mode — this is dark-only
- ❌ Emojis in any UI text (including AI-generated content)
- ❌ Words: "habit", "task", "goal", "journal", "diary", "chatbot", "assistant", "score"
- ✅ Use instead: "Protocol", "Execution", "Signal Log", "System", "Momentum Index"
- ❌ Success toasts with "Great job!" — use clinical confirmations ("Execution logged.")
- ❌ Gradient backgrounds on screens — surfaces are flat dark, gradients only on buttons/progress elements
- ❌ Illustrations, icons with personality, mascots

